# Clyro

PyQt6 Windows desktop media optimizer architecture scaffold.

- Migration plan: `CLOP_WINDOWS_PYQT6_MIGRATION_PLAN.md`
- Architecture blueprint: `CLOP_WINDOWS_PYQT6_ARCHITECTURE_BLUEPRINT.md`

## Current slice status

Implemented:

1. End-to-end `optimise` CLI flow for image + video + PDF files with queue-backed execution.
2. Layered flow: `presentation -> application -> domain -> infrastructure`.
3. Image optimization backend:
   - `pngquant` for PNG when available
   - `jpegoptim` for JPEG when available
   - Pillow fallback when binaries are unavailable
4. Settings-driven image behavior:
   - persisted JSON settings at `%APPDATA%\\Clyro\\settings.json`
   - preferred output format (`keep/jpeg/webp/png`) with alpha fallback
   - metadata preserve/strip policy
   - GIF processing opt-in
   - skip-if-larger control integrated via settings + command flags
5. Output template + output path policy.
6. Phosphor SVG icon registry wired to local asset folder (`src/clyro/assets/SVGs`).
7. Process runner supports live stdout/stderr output callbacks.
8. Process runner supports hard cancellation checks for long-running subprocesses.
9. Local IPC server endpoints:
   - `GET /health`
   - `POST /optimise` (optional token via `X-Clyro-Token`, `?wait=0` async)
   - `GET /jobs` and `GET /jobs/<job_id>`
   - `POST /stop` (`{"job_id": "<id>"}` or `{"all": true}` / `?all=1`)
10. Minimal PyQt floating results window:
   - choose image files
   - run optimisation via queue service
   - show per-file progress bars for queued/running jobs
   - cancel latest active job from UI
11. Test coverage:
    - unit tests for use case/queue/IPC/process runner/UI VM
    - integration tests for settings-driven image format, metadata, and larger-output skip behavior
    - integration tests for video metadata probing, FFmpeg filter command building, progress parsing, and cancellation
    - integration tests for PDF validation, Ghostscript progress mapping, larger-output skip behavior, and cancellation
12. PDF crop/uncrop operations:
    - `crop-pdf` command (left/right/top/bottom margins in points)
    - `uncrop-pdf` command (restore crop box to media box)
    - requires `pypdf` for crop/uncrop support
13. Orchestrator and in-memory state store:
    - `OptimisationOrchestrator` wraps queue submission/list/get/wait/stop APIs
    - `AppStateStore` tracks job lifecycle snapshots (progress/status/result summaries)
    - richer batch summaries in CLI/IPC (bytes + media-type counts)

CLI usage:

```powershell
$env:PYTHONPATH=\"src\"
python -m clyro.presentation.cli.main optimise .\path\to\image.jpg
python -m clyro.presentation.cli.main optimise .\path\to\image.jpg --json
python -m clyro.presentation.cli.main optimise .\path\to\clip.mp4 --video-fps-cap 30 --video-max-width 1280 --video-force-aac
python -m clyro.presentation.cli.main optimise .\path\to\clip.mp4 --video-remove-audio --video-playback-speed 1.25 --video-crop 1280:720:0:0
python -m clyro.presentation.cli.main optimise .\path\to\doc.pdf --aggressive
python -m clyro.presentation.cli.main crop-pdf .\path\to\doc.pdf --left 18 --right 18 --top 24 --bottom 24
python -m clyro.presentation.cli.main uncrop-pdf .\path\to\doc.pdf --in-place
```
